# Allowlist: central core files with known provider/OS coupling and bash shebangs.
#
# Format:
#   <path>:<reason>
#
# Reason prefixes determine which check accepts the entry:
#   provider/OS reference - ...  — accepted by the provider/OS ID check
#   bash shebang - ...           — accepted by the bash language policy check
#
# Every provider/OS entry below is tracked Phase 3 extraction debt: the literal
# exists in core today and will move into the owning provider/plugin during
# Phase 3. No silent passes — if the scan finds a literal not listed here, the
# boundary check fails.

# --- Provider/OS coupling (Phase 3 extraction debt) ---
eve_sdk/config.py:provider/OS reference - provider-keyed env-var table - Phase 3: provider env table extraction
eve_sdk/resolve.py:provider/OS reference - provider branches and image-field env emission - Phase 3: provider env emission extraction
scripts/doctor:provider/OS reference - provider-specific CLI tool checks - Phase 3: moves into provider plugins
scripts/instance-create:provider/OS reference - provider-specific CLI usage hints - Phase 3: derives from provider manifests
scripts/instance-password:provider/OS reference - vultr-specific password retrieval - Phase 3: moves into vultr plugin
scripts/instance-profile-overlay:provider/OS reference - raspberry-pi host validation - Phase 3: moves into raspberry-pi plugin
scripts/package-provision:provider/OS reference - raspberry-pi password handling - Phase 3: moves into raspberry-pi plugin
scripts/profile-resolve:provider/OS reference - provider-specific env emission - Phase 3: moves into provider plugins
scripts/providers-status:provider/OS reference - provider-specific connectivity checks - Phase 3: moves into provider plugins
scripts/provision:provider/OS reference - vultr-specific password retrieval - Phase 3: moves into vultr plugin
scripts/remote-console:provider/OS reference - local-qemu not-implemented guard - Phase 3: moves into local-qemu plugin
scripts/remote-waypipe:provider/OS reference - raspberry-pi IP handling - Phase 3: moves into raspberry-pi plugin
scripts/vagrant-up:provider/OS reference - local-qemu Vagrant dispatch - Phase 3: moves into local-qemu plugin

